{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":61207,"duration_api_ms":62468,"ttft_ms":2431,"num_turns":1,"result":"I'll register a task with the Centian workflow, then retrieve the API docs and fix the bug using TDD.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Fc6FiXQ7h58t3SKBYnhPJ1\",\"name\":\"mcp__centian__guided_tdd_workflow\",\"input\":{\"action\":\"register_task\",\"task_description\":\"Fix 400 error when free-plan users create additional users via MyOrgAPI. The bug is in user_payload.py which builds the API payload.\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fc6FiXQ7h58t3SKBYnhPJ1\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n \\\"task_id\\\": \\\"task_bb05c191\\\",\\n \\\"status\\\": \\\"registered\\\",\\n \\\"current_phase\\\": \\\"understand\\\",\\n \\\"message\\\": \\\"Task registered. Phase: understand. Read existing code and docs before writing tests.\\\",\\n \\\"hints\\\": [\\n \\\"Use `get_docs` from the docs MCP to retrieve the MyOrgAPI spec.\\\",\\n \\\"Read `user_payload.py` to understand current behavior.\\\",\\n \\\"Read `test_user_payload.py` to understand existing coverage.\\\"\\n ]\\n}\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nTask registered. Now let me retrieve the API documentation and read the existing code.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PU23MNLNM6eHmx3R3XbFmz\",\"name\":\"mcp__docs__get_docs\",\"input\":{\"topic\":\"MyOrgAPI\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PU23MNLNM6eHmx3R3XbFmz\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# MyOrgAPI – User Creation Endpoint\\n\\n## POST /org/{org_id}/users\\n\\nCreates a new user within the given organisation (tenant).\\n\\n### Request body (JSON)\\n\\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\\n| `name` | string | yes | Display name of the new user. |\\n| `email` | string | yes | Email address (must be unique within the org). |\\n| `role` | string | yes | One of: `admin`, `member`, `viewer`. |\\n| `plan_context` | object | **conditional** | Billing context. Required when the org is on a **paid** plan. **Must be omitted (or set to `null`) for free-plan orgs.** |\\n\\n### plan_context object (paid plans only)\\n\\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\\n| `plan_id` | string | yes | The identifier of the current billing plan. |\\n| `seat_count` | integer | yes | Current seat count *after* adding this user. |\\n\\n### Validation rules\\n\\n* If `plan_context` is present and the org is on the **free** plan, the API returns **400 Bad Request** with body `{\\\"error\\\": \\\"plan_context not allowed for free-tier orgs\\\"}`.\\n* If `plan_context` is missing and the org is on a **paid** plan, the API returns **400 Bad Request** with body `{\\\"error\\\": \\\"plan_context required for paid orgs\\\"}`.\\n\\n### Example – free plan\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n \\\"name\\\": \\\"Alice\\\",\\n \\\"email\\\": \\\"alice@example.com\\\",\\n \\\"role\\\": \\\"member\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Example – paid plan\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n \\\"name\\\": \\\"Bob\\\",\\n \\\"email\\\": \\\"bob@example.com\\\",\\n \\\"role\\\": \\\"member\\\",\\n \\\"plan_context\\\": {\\n \\\"plan_id\\\": \\\"plan_pro_v2\\\",\\n \\\"seat_count\\\": 5\\n }\\n}\\n```\\n\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nNow I understand the issue. The API returns 400 if `plan_context` is present for free-plan orgs. Let me read the existing code.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01MivGqTe6QBVnrfyJp6sRhN\",\"name\":\"read_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"user_payload.py\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01MivGqTe6QBVnrfyJp6sRhN\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Build the JSON payload for POST /org/{org_id}/users.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n\\ndef build_user_payload(name: str, email: str, role: str, plan: dict | None = None) -> dict:\\n \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the request body dict for creating an org user.\\n\\n Parameters\\n ----------\\n name: display name\\n email: unique email within the org\\n role: one of 'admin', 'member', 'viewer'\\n plan: dict with 'plan_id' and 'seat_count' for paid plans, or None for free\\n \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n payload: dict = {\\n \\\"name\\\": name,\\n \\\"email\\\": email,\\n \\\"role\\\": role,\\n \\\"plan_context\\\": {\\n \\\"plan_id\\\": plan[\\\"plan_id\\\"] if plan else \\\"none\\\",\\n \\\"seat_count\\\": plan[\\\"seat_count\\\"] if plan else 0,\\n },\\n }\\n return payload\\n\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01XnwJVDjejJ1QdqTNnxWrqx\",\"name\":\"read_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"test_user_payload.py\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XnwJVDjejJ1QdqTNnxWrqx\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Existing regression tests for build_user_payload – DO NOT MODIFY.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport unittest\\n\\nfrom user_payload import build_user_payload\\n\\n\\nclass TestPaidPlanPayload(unittest.TestCase):\\n \\\"\\\"\\\"Verify correct payload for paid-plan orgs.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n def test_includes_plan_context(self):\\n plan = {\\\"plan_id\\\": \\\"plan_pro_v2\\\", \\\"seat_count\\\": 5}\\n result = build_user_payload(\\\"Bob\\\", \\\"bob@example.com\\\", \\\"member\\\", plan=plan)\\n self.assertEqual(result[\\\"plan_context\\\"][\\\"plan_id\\\"], \\\"plan_pro_v2\\\")\\n self.assertEqual(result[\\\"plan_context\\\"][\\\"seat_count\\\"], 5)\\n\\n def test_basic_fields_present(self):\\n plan = {\\\"plan_id\\\": \\\"plan_pro_v2\\\", \\\"seat_count\\\": 3}\\n result = build_user_payload(\\\"Eve\\\", \\\"eve@example.com\\\", \\\"admin\\\", plan=plan)\\n self.assertEqual(result[\\\"name\\\"], \\\"Eve\\\")\\n self.assertEqual(result[\\\"email\\\"], \\\"eve@example.com\\\")\\n self.assertEqual(result[\\\"role\\\"], \\\"admin\\\")\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n unittest.main()\\n\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nFound the bug: `build_user_payload` always includes `plan_context` even for free-plan orgs (when `plan` is `None`), which causes the API to return 400. Now let me advance to the test phase and write a failing regression test.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01TRHmbbLUgsDqaK3Bpwsj6X\",\"name\":\"mcp__centian__guided_tdd_workflow\",\"input\":{\"action\":\"advance_phase\",\"task_id\":\"task_bb05c191\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TRHmbbLUgsDqaK3Bpwsj6X\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n \\\"task_id\\\": \\\"task_bb05c191\\\",\\n \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n \\\"current_phase\\\": \\\"write_failing_test\\\",\\n \\\"message\\\": \\\"Phase: write_failing_test. Write a unittest in `test_regression.py` that exposes the bug (must FAIL against current code).\\\",\\n \\\"hints\\\": [\\n \\\"The test should assert the correct behavior for free-plan users based on the API spec.\\\",\\n \\\"Run the test to confirm it fails before fixing anything.\\\"\\n ]\\n}\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nWriting a failing regression test that asserts `plan_context` must not be present for free-plan users.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015AeVf1HGfLDpYeiFxGpbNE\",\"name\":\"write_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"test_regression.py\",\"content\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Regression test for free-plan user creation bug.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport unittest\\n\\nfrom user_payload import build_user_payload\\n\\n\\nclass TestFreePlanPayloadRegression(unittest.TestCase):\\n \\\"\\\"\\\"Free-plan orgs must NOT include plan_context in the payload.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n def test_free_plan_omits_plan_context(self):\\n result = build_user_payload(\\\"Alice\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"member\\\", plan=None)\\n self.assertNotIn(\\\"plan_context\\\", result)\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n unittest.main()\\n\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015AeVf1HGfLDpYeiFxGpbNE\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nNow let me run the test to confirm it fails.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015DJVpPcfkCsXbq8hMkBwmB\",\"name\":\"execute\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"cd /Users/brb/projects/centian-benchmarks/.centian/benchmarks/context_sprawl_v1/20260515133859_current_claude_run/runs/current_claude_bug_fix_v1_attempt_001/project && python -m pytest test_regression.py -v 2>&1 || python -m unittest test_regression -v 2>&1\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015DJVpPcfkCsXbq8hMkBwmB\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"test_free_plan_omits_plan_context (test_regression.TestFreePlanPayloadRegression.test_free_plan_omits_plan_context) ... FAIL\\n\\n======================================================================\\nFAIL: test_free_plan_omits_plan_context (test_regression.TestFreePlanPayloadRegression.test_free_plan_omits_plan_context)\\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\\nTraceback (most recent call last):\\n  File \\\"/Users/brb/projects/centian-benchmarks/.centian/benchmarks/context_sprawl_v1/20260515133859_current_claude_run/runs/current_claude_bug_fix_v1_attempt_001/project/test_regression.py\\\", line 13, in test_free_plan_omits_plan_context\\n    self.assertNotIn(\\\"plan_context\\\", result)\\nAssertionError: 'plan_context' unexpectedly found in {'name': 'Alice', 'email': 'alice@example.com', 'role': 'member', 'plan_context': {'plan_id': 'none', 'seat_count': 0}}\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\\nRan 1 test in 0.000s\\n\\nFAILED (failures=1)\\n\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nTest fails as expected. Now advancing to the fix phase.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01KFcqkNqxjzVT5SzNMaWN6y\",\"name\":\"mcp__centian__guided_tdd_workflow\",\"input\":{\"action\":\"advance_phase\",\"task_id\":\"task_bb05c191\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01KFcqkNqxjzVT5SzNMaWN6y\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n \\\"task_id\\\": \\\"task_bb05c191\\\",\\n \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n \\\"current_phase\\\": \\\"implement_fix\\\",\\n \\\"message\\\": \\\"Phase: implement_fix. Make the minimal change to `user_payload.py` so the failing test passes without breaking existing tests.\\\",\\n \\\"hints\\\": [\\n \\\"Only include `plan_context` when the caller supplies a plan dict.\\\",\\n \\\"Run both test files after your change.\\\"\\n ]\\n}\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nImplementing the minimal fix — only include `plan_context` when a plan is provided.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DFG6ixGPkh5E3gPdM2kpUv\",\"name\":\"write_file\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"user_payload.py\",\"content\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Build the JSON payload for POST /org/{org_id}/users.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n\\ndef build_user_payload(name: str, email: str, role: str, plan: dict | None = None) -> dict:\\n \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the request body dict for creating an org user.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n payload: dict = {\\n \\\"name\\\": name,\\n \\\"email\\\": email,\\n \\\"role\\\": role,\\n }\\n if plan is not None:\\n payload[\\\"plan_context\\\"] = {\\n \\\"plan_id\\\": plan[\\\"plan_id\\\"],\\n \\\"seat_count\\\": plan[\\\"seat_count\\\"],\\n }\\n return payload\\n\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DFG6ixGPkh5E3gPdM2kpUv\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nRunning both test files to confirm everything passes.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01VU3BDr2H4ULqWU22W31sHp\",\"name\":\"execute\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"cd /Users/brb/projects/centian-benchmarks/.centian/benchmarks/context_sprawl_v1/20260515133859_current_claude_run/runs/current_claude_bug_fix_v1_attempt_001/project && python -m unittest test_regression test_user_payload -v 2>&1\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01VU3BDr2H4ULqWU22W31sHp\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"test_free_plan_omits_plan_context (test_regression.TestFreePlanPayloadRegression.test_free_plan_omits_plan_context) ... ok\\ntest_basic_fields_present (test_user_payload.TestPaidPlanPayload.test_basic_fields_present) ... ok\\ntest_includes_plan_context (test_user_payload.TestPaidPlanPayload.test_includes_plan_context) ... ok\\n\\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\\nRan 3 tests in 0.000s\\n\\nOK\\n\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\nAll 3 tests pass. Advancing to complete the task.\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01MkNnZvAGpWx1MQK7RYmojJ\",\"name\":\"mcp__centian__guided_tdd_workflow\",\"input\":{\"action\":\"advance_phase\",\"task_id\":\"task_bb05c191\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01MkNnZvAGpWx1MQK7RYmojJ\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n \\\"task_id\\\": \\\"task_bb05c191\\\",\\n \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n \\\"current_phase\\\": \\\"verify\\\",\\n \\\"message\\\": \\\"Phase: verify. Run ALL tests one final time and confirm green.\\\",\\n \\\"hints\\\": [\\n \\\"Run both `test_user_payload.py` and `test_regression.py`.\\\",\\n \\\"If green, advance to complete the task.\\\"\\n ]\\n}\"}]}\n</tool_result>\n\n<tool_use>\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01XAFLH2SFh1r1a8PqZLpNT2\",\"name\":\"execute\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"cd /Users/brb/projects/centian-benchmarks/.centian/benchmarks/context_sprawl_v1/20260515133859_current_claude_run/runs/current_claude_bug_fix_v1_attempt_001/project && python -m unittest discover -s . -p 'test_*.py' -v 2>&1\"}}\n</tool_use>\n<tool_result>\n{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XAFLH2SFh1r1a8PqZLpNT2\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"test_free_plan_omits_plan_context (test_regression.TestFreePlanPayloadRegression.